#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:601
msgid "Engineers"
msgstr "Einnseanairean"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:422
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Engineers are similar to Settlers, but they work twice as fast and move "
"twice as fast. Engineers may also perform major terrain transformations (for "
"example, converting Tundra into Desert) which are beyond the capabilities of "
"Settlers. See the Terrain Alterations section for more details."
msgstr ""
"Tha einnseanairean car coltach ris na tuinichean ach tha iad ag obair agus "
"a' gluasad dà thuras cho luath.  'S urrainn do dh'einnseanairean talamh "
"cruth-atharrachadh cuideachd (mar eisimpleir, nì iad fàsach de thundra), rud "
"nach urrainn do thuiniche sam bith a dhèanamh; faic an earrann air "
"'Atharrachadh na talamhainn' airson barrachd fiosrachaidh."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:428
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"TIP 1: Upgrade Settlers to Engineers when possible, as Engineers require the "
"same resources as ordinary Settlers."
msgstr ""
"GLIOCAS 1:  Àrdaich tuinichean 'nan einnseanairean ma bhios cothrom agad sin "
"a dhèanamh, feumaidh einnseanairean an dearbh bheòshlaint 's a dh'fheumas "
"tuinichean àbhaisteach."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:431
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"TIP 2: If you manage to build Leonardo's Workshop, research Explosives "
"before the Workshop becomes obsolete. This way, your Settler units will be "
"upgraded for free."
msgstr ""
"GLIOCAS 2:  Ma thèid agad air Bùth-obrach Leonardo a thogail, rannsaich "
"stuthan-spreadhaidh mus dèid Bùth-obrach Leonardo o fheum.  Ma nì thu seo, "
"thèid na tuinichean agad àrdachadh saor an-asgaidh."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:438 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:643
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:581 data/experimental/units.ruleset:603
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:582 data/royale/units.ruleset:735
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:647
msgid "Warriors"
msgstr "Cathaich"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:501 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:706
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:644 data/experimental/units.ruleset:666
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:645 data/royale/units.ruleset:798
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:710
msgid "Archers"
msgstr "Boghadairean"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:527 data/classic/units.ruleset:670
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:692 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:671
msgid ""
"Archers fight with bows and arrows and have a good offensive value as well "
"as decent defense."
msgstr ""
"Nì boghadairean sabaid le boghan is saighdean agus tha iad math a' toirt "
"ionnsaigh agus a' dìon."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:565 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:770
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:708 data/experimental/units.ruleset:730
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:709 data/royale/units.ruleset:862
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:774
msgid "Pikemen"
msgstr "Pìcearan"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:595 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:796
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:892 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:800
msgid ""
"Equipped with long pikes, Pikemen replaces Phalanx as the preferred city "
"defender."
msgstr ""
"Tha pìcean fada aig pìcearan agus tha iad a' dol an àite nam falangasan mar "
"phrìomh dhìonadair nam bailtean."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:628 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:829
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:772 data/experimental/units.ruleset:794
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:773 data/royale/units.ruleset:925
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:833
msgid ""
"Musketeers are infantry equipped with early firearms and replace Pikemen as "
"the preferred city defender."
msgstr ""
"'S e coisridh a tha ann am musgadairean aig a bheil airm-losgaidh thràtha "
"agus tha iad a' dol an àite nam pìcearan mar am prìomh aonad a chum dìon "
"baile."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:635 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:944
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:780 data/royale/units.ruleset:1086
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:948
msgid "Fanatics"
msgstr "Fanataich"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:662 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:973
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:807 data/royale/units.ruleset:1115
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:977
msgid "Fanatics are warriors extremely devoted to a higher cause."
msgstr "'S e cathaich a tha ann am fanataich a tha ro dhìleas do àrd-chùis."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:664 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:809
msgid ""
"Fundamentalist nations can maintain Fanatic units without having to pay any "
"shields for upkeep."
msgstr ""
"Cumaidh nàiseanan bun-chreidmheach aonadan fanatach agus cha bhi aca "
"sgiathan beòshlaint a phàigheadh air an son."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:670 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:902
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:779 data/experimental/units.ruleset:801
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:815 data/royale/units.ruleset:1043
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:906
msgid "Partisan"
msgstr "Partasan"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:696 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:930
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:805 data/experimental/units.ruleset:827
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:841 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:934
msgid ""
"Partisans are guerilla fighters who are experts at using the terrain to "
"their advantage."
msgstr ""
"'S e sabaidichean guerilla a tha ann am partasain a tha fìor eòlach air "
"cruth na tìre 's a chleachdas an t-èolas seo ann an sabaid."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:699
msgid ""
"A number of Partisans are granted free when an enemy conquers your city -- "
"they automatically assume defensive positions in the surrounding countryside "
"-- but only under these conditions:\n"
" - Guerilla Warfare must be known by at least one player.\n"
" - You must be the player who originally built the city.\n"
" - You must know about Communism and Gunpowder.\n"
" - You must run either a Democracy or a Communist government."
msgstr ""
"Gheibh thu grunn phartasan saor an-asgaidh nuair a cheannsaicheas nàmhaid "
"baile agad -- bheir iad orra àitichean dìon san sgìre mun cuairt air a' "
"bhaile -- ach a-mhàin san t-suidheachadh a leanas:\n"
" - Feumaidh cogadh guerilla a bhith rannsaichte aig aon chluicheadair air a' "
"char as lugha.\n"
" - Feumaidh gur thuse an neach a stèidhich am baile o thùs.\n"
" - Feumaidh eòlas a bhith agad air co-mhaoineas agus fùdar-gunna.\n"
" - Feumaidh riaghaltas deamocratach no co-mhaoineach a bhith agad."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:710 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:868
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:819 data/experimental/units.ruleset:841
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:855 data/royale/units.ruleset:1009
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:872
msgid "Alpine Troops"
msgstr "Feachdan ailpeach"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:736 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:896
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:845 data/experimental/units.ruleset:867
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:881 data/royale/units.ruleset:1037
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:900
msgid "Alpine Troops are highly mobile units as well as excellent defenders."
msgstr ""
"Tha feachdan ailpeach fìor mhath air gluasad mun cuairt agus tha iad "
"anabarrach math air an dìon."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:800 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1010
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:909 data/experimental/units.ruleset:931
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:945 data/royale/units.ruleset:1151
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1014
msgid "Marines are infantry who are experts at marine warfare."
msgstr ""
"'S e coisridh a tha sàr-eòlach air cogadh na mara a tha anns na saighdearan-"
"mara."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:831 data/classic/units.ruleset:940
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:976
msgid ""
"Paratroopers are experts at airborne attacks. From a friendly city or "
"airbase, Paratroopers who have not expended any movement points can paradrop "
"directly to any tile in range, and be immediately ready to act there. "
"(Beware dropping into unseen territory, as Paratroopers landing on a tile "
"occupied by enemy units are easy targets!)"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:868 data/classic/units.ruleset:977
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1000 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1013
msgid ""
"The Mechanized Infantry has the strongest defensive strength of any land "
"unit, but is only available near the end of the technology tree."
msgstr ""
"'S a' choisridh mheacanaichte an t-aonad talamhainn aig a bheil neart dìon "
"as àirde ach chan fhaighear seo ach aig ceann thall craobh na teicneolasan."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:875 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1089
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:984 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1007
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1020 data/royale/units.ruleset:1232
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1093
msgid "Horsemen"
msgstr "Marcshluagh"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:901 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1115
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1010 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1033
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1046 data/royale/units.ruleset:1258
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1119
msgid ""
"Horsemen are mounted warriors and an early shock-troop that can penetrate "
"deep into enemy territory."
msgstr ""
"'S e cathaich air muin each a tha san mharcshluagh, ceatharn luath a thèid a-"
"steach domhain air àrainn nàimhdeil agus a nochd tràth san eachdraidh."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:934 data/classic/units.ruleset:1043
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1066 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1079
msgid ""
"Chariots are horse-pulled war wagons, stronger but more expensive than "
"horsemen."
msgstr ""
"'S e carbadan cogaidh each-tharraingte a tha ann an carbadan, nas làidire "
"agus nas daoire na marcshluagh."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:940 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1158
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1085 data/royale/units.ruleset:1301
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1162
msgid "Elephants"
msgstr "Ailbhein"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:966 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1111
msgid ""
"Elephants are towering animals trained for war that are often used as "
"powerful shock troops, but defend poorly against most other units."
msgstr ""
"Tha ailbhein 'nam beathaichean mòra àrda a chaidh an trèanadh airson cogadh "
"agus thathar 'gan cleachdadh gus eagal a chur air nàmhaid ach chan eil iad "
"ro mhath 'gan dìon fhèin."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:972 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1190
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1117 data/royale/units.ruleset:1333
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1194
msgid "Crusaders"
msgstr "Ridirean-croise"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:998 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1216
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1220
msgid ""
"Crusaders are highly disciplined mounted warriors driven by a higher cause."
msgstr ""
"Tha ridirean-croise 'nan cathaich dheagh smachdaichte air muin each agus aig "
"a bheil àrd-chùis."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1036 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1254
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1081 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1104
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1181 data/royale/units.ruleset:1400
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1258
msgid "Dragoons"
msgstr "Saighdear-eachraidh"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1063 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1280
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1108 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1131
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1208 data/royale/units.ruleset:1426
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1284
msgid "Dragoons are mounted warriors carrying early firearms."
msgstr ""
"'S e cathaich air muin each a tha ann an saighdearan-eachraidh aig a bheil "
"airm-losgaidh thràtha."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1094 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1311
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1139 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1162
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1239 data/royale/units.ruleset:1457
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1315
msgid "Cavalry are mounted and highly trained soldiers."
msgstr ""
"'S e saighdearean air muin each agus a fhuair deagh thrèanadh a tha san "
"eachdraidh."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1225 data/classic/units.ruleset:1270
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1293 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1370
msgid ""
"The artillery is an upgraded cannon. It is a very strong attacker but "
"equally weak defender and will need an escort to be effective."
msgstr ""
"'S canan leasaichte a tha san airtilearaidh. Tha iad glè làidir a' toirt "
"ionnsaigh ach chan eil ach comas dìon lag annta agus feumaidh iad "
"coimheadachd mus bi iad èifeachdach."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1232 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1456
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1277 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1300
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1377 data/royale/units.ruleset:1609
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1460
msgid "Howitzer"
msgstr "Hòbhaitsear"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1258 data/classic/units.ruleset:1303
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1326 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1403
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Howitzers are upgraded artillery with improved defensive as well as "
"offensive capabilities. They can shoot over city walls, ignoring their "
"effect."
msgstr ""
"'S airtilearaidh leasaichte a tha san hòbhaitsear aig a bheil an dà chuid "
"comasan dìon is ionnsaighe nas fhearr."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1363 data/classic/units.ruleset:1409
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The Helicopter is a very powerful unit, as it can both fly and conquer "
"cities. Care must be exercised, because Helicopters lose a small amount of "
"health for every turn not spent in a city or airbase or on a Carrier, unless "
"you have the United Nations wonder, and Helicopters may be attacked by "
"ground units."
msgstr ""
"'S e aonad glè chumhachdach a tha ann an heileacoptair a chionn 's gun "
"urrainn dha itealaich agus bailtean a cheannsachadh.  Feumaidh tu an deagh "
"chùram a ghabhail oir caillidh heileacoptairean beagan slàinte gach cuairt "
"mur eil iad ann am baile no bunait adhair no air giùlanair agus mur eil "
"mìorbhail nan Nàiseanan Aonaichte agad, 's urrainn do dh'aonadan talamhainn "
"ionnsaigh a thoirt air heileacoptairean."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1372 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1610
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1418 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1442
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1517 data/royale/units.ruleset:1759
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1614
msgid "Stealth Fighter"
msgstr "Sabaidiche dìth-chealtair"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1404 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1638
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1787 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1642
msgid "An improved Fighter, with improved attack and a higher movement radius."
msgstr ""
"'S e sabaidiche leasaichte a tha ann aig a bheil comas ionnsaigh nas fhearr "
"agus puingean gluasaid a bharrachd."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1410 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1644
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1457 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1481
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1556 data/royale/units.ruleset:1793
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1648
msgid "Stealth Bomber"
msgstr "Bomadair dìth-chealtair"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1436 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1671
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1485 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1509
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1584 data/royale/units.ruleset:1820
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1675
msgid "An improved Bomber, with improved attack and a higher movement radius."
msgstr ""
"'S e bomadair leasaichte a tha ann aig a bheil comas ionnsaigh nas fhearr "
"agus puingean gluasaid a bharrachd."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1470
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The Trireme is your first boat unit. It can act as a transport ship and has "
"rudimentary offensive capabilities. If it ends its turn away from shore, it "
"has a 1/2 chance of sinking. This is reduced to 1/3 after Seafaring, 1/4 "
"after Navigation, and eliminated by the Lighthouse wonder."
msgstr ""
"'S e an trì-ràmhach a' chiad aonad bàta a bhios agad. 'S urrainn dha aonadan "
"a ghiùlan agus tha comas beag ionnsaigh ann ach chan urrainn dha seòladh air "
"leacagan an aiginn."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1479 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1713
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1526 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1551
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1625 data/royale/units.ruleset:2004
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1717
msgid "Caravel"
msgstr "Carbhal"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1506
msgid ""
"The Caravel replaces the Trireme and is much more reliable on the open seas."
msgstr ""
"Tha carbhalan a' dol an àite nan trì-ràmhaich agus tha iad fada nas "
"earbsaiche air a' chuan mhòr."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1512 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1747
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1559 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1584
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1658 data/royale/units.ruleset:2038
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1752
msgid "Galleon"
msgstr "Gailleon"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1539 data/classic/units.ruleset:1586
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1611 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1685
msgid ""
"The Galleon is a pure transport ship and cannot attack other ships, though "
"it may still defend itself when attacked."
msgstr ""
"Chan eil sa ghailleon ach bàta giùlain agus chan urrainn dha ionnsaigh a "
"thoirt air bàtaichean eile ged a tha e comasach air a dhìon fhèin ma "
"bheirear ionnsaigh air-san."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1613 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1845
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1660 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1685
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1759 data/royale/units.ruleset:2172
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1850
msgid "Destroyer"
msgstr "Sgriosadair"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1639 data/classic/units.ruleset:1686
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1711 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1785
msgid "An improved Ironclad, with better move rate and vision."
msgstr ""
"'S e bàta iarann-sligeach leasaichte a tha ann aig a bheil comas gluasaid is "
"lèirsinn nas fhearr."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1641 data/classic/units.ruleset:1688
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1713 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1787
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"TIP: A very fast unit, which is very useful for hunting down enemy "
"Transports."
msgstr ""
"GLIOCAS:  Aonad fìor luath a tha glè fheumail gus giùlanairean nàimhdeil a "
"shealg."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1678 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1915
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1725 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1750
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1824 data/royale/units.ruleset:2242
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1920
msgid "AEGIS Cruiser"
msgstr "Crùsair AEGIS"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1708 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1945
msgid ""
"The AEGIS Cruiser is equipped with an advanced defensive missile system."
msgstr ""
"Tha airm itealach adhartach aig crùsairean AEGIS leis an dìon iad iad fhèin."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1851 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2102
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1899 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1925
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1998 data/royale/units.ruleset:2523
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2114
msgid "Cruise Missile"
msgstr "Cruise Missile"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1877 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2129
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1925 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1952
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2024 data/royale/units.ruleset:2550
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2141
msgid ""
"The Cruise Missile is a long-distance missile that can strike deep into "
"enemy territory."
msgstr ""
"Tha an Cruise Missile 'na arm itealach a ruigeas cinn-uidhe fad air falbh "
"agus an teis-mheadhain dùthaich do nàmhaid."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1880 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2132
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1928 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1955
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2027 data/royale/units.ruleset:2553
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2144
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"TIP: A handful of these can successfully keep the waters around your "
"treasured homeland free of enemy ships."
msgstr ""
"GLIOCAS:  Bidh badan dhiubh gu math èifeachdach gus am muir mun cuairt air "
"do dhùthaich phrìseil a chumail saor o bhàtaichean do nàimhdean."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1921 data/classic/units.ruleset:1977
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2004 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2076
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"TIP 1: Nuking the ocean will not generate fallout, and is a most effective "
"(but expensive!!) way of getting rid of enemy ships."
msgstr ""
"GLIOCAS 1: Chan adhbharaich spreadhadh niùclasach air a' chuan sileadh "
"niùclasach agus 's e dòigh èifeachdach (ach daor) gus faighinn cuidhteas de "
"shoithichean nàimhdeil."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1925
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"TIP 2: You may be involved in a situation where you've invaded an enemy "
"country en masse, but the enemy cities are too strong. Before using a "
"Nuclear unit, assemble a gang of Settlers and/or Engineers next to the city "
"and have them ready to fix the fallout on the same turn it occurs!  This "
"minimizes the chance of global warming. Eco-friendly nukes!"
msgstr ""
"GLIOCAS 2:  Faodaidh gun dig latha 's tu air briseadh a-steach air dùthaich "
"le arm mòr ach bailtean nàimhdeil a tha ro làidir.  Mus cleachd thu arm "
"niùclasach, cruinnich buidheann de thuinichean agus/no einnseanairean faisg "
"air a' bhaile ach am bi iad ri do làimh gus an sileadh niùclasach a ghlanadh "
"san dearbh chuairt 's a nochdas e! Lùghdaichidh seo cunnart de gheamhradh "
"niùclasach.  Ionnsaigh niùclasach èiceolach!"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1966
msgid ""
"A Diplomat is an official that carries your dispatches and is authorized to "
"deal with foreign dignitaries. He may also undertake various covert "
"operations with the intent of harming your opponents; Diplomats in your own "
"cities defend them against such actions."
msgstr ""
"'S e oifigear a tha ann an dìoplomat a ghiùlaineas do theachdaireachdan agus "
"aig a bheil ùghdarras dèiligeadh ri uaislean dìoplomasach. 'S urrainn dha "
"grunn ghnìomhan dìomhair a chur an gnìomh cuideachd a chuireas dochann air "
"do nàimhdean; dìonaidh dìoplomatan 'nad bhailtean fhèin an aghaidh gnìomhan "
"mar seo."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:1976
msgid ""
"If a foreign unit is alone on a tile, you may attempt to bribe it with your "
"Diplomat. By paying a sum of gold the unit will immediately become yours; "
"the exact sum depends on the status of the unit and that of the civilization "
"owning it. However, units belonging to Democratic governments cannot be "
"bribed. Bribery when not at war will cause a diplomatic incident."
msgstr ""
"Ma bhios aonad cèin air leacag leis fhèin, 's urrainn dhut feuchainn ri brìb "
"a thoirt dha leis an dìoplomat agad. Le bhith a' pàigheadh suim a dh'òr, "
"bidh an t-aonad agad-sa sa bhad; tha an t-suim fhèin a' crochadh air staid "
"an aonaid agus an t-sìobhaltais aig a bheil e. Chan urrainn dhut aonadan a "
"tha aig riaghaltas deamocrasach a bhrìbeadh ge-tà. Ma bhrìbeas tu aonad rè "
"àm sìthe, adhbharaichidh tu connspaid dhìoplomasach."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2023 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2299
msgid ""
"In some game strategies, hordes of Diplomats can be used to wreak havoc on "
"the enemy.  Little wonder that Diplomats are often viewed with suspicion and "
"fear!"
msgstr ""
"Tha cuid a ro-innleachdan cluiche ann a chleachdas prasgain de dhìoplomatan "
"gus nàmhaid a chur ann an mì-rian mòr. Chan iongnadh gu bheil mì-earbsa is "
"eagal air daoine ro dhìoplomatan!"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2030 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2309
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2098 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2125
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2197 data/royale/units.ruleset:2837
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2381
msgid "Spy"
msgstr "Brathadair"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2061 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2350
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2138 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2165
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2237 data/royale/units.ruleset:2877
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2422
msgid ""
"A Spy is more skilled in the arts of espionage than her Diplomat predecessor."
msgstr ""
"Tha brathadairean nas ealanta air brathadaireachd na tha na dìoplomatan a "
"bha agad roimhpe."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2063 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2352
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2140 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2239
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2424
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"She can perform all the functions of the Diplomat. Refer to the Diplomat "
"entry for more details. Unlike a Diplomat, a Spy may also survive an "
"operation in a foreign city and become more experienced as a result. Spies "
"are also more effective than Diplomats at defending cities against foreign "
"Diplomats and Spies."
msgstr ""
"'S urrainn dhi gach rud a dhèanamh fhathast a rinn na dìoplomatan; thoir "
"sùil air an fhiosrachadh mu na dìoplomatan airson mion-fhiosrachadh. Mairidh "
"brathadair beò ma nì iad obair brathadaireachd ann am baile cèin, rud nach "
"b' urrainn dhan dìoplomat, agus fàsaidh iad nas ealanta ri linn sin. Tha "
"brathadairean nas èifeachdaiche ann an dìon nam bailtean an aghaidh "
"brathadairean is dìoplomatan cèin na bha na dìoplomatan iad fhèin."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2069 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2245
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A Spy can also be used to:\n"
"\n"
" - sabotage an enemy unit (reducing its hit points to half), if it is alone "
"on a tile and the players are at war;\n"
" - poison the water supply of an enemy city (reducing the population by "
"one);\n"
" - steal specific technology (with a reduced chance of success);\n"
" - steal further technologies from a city which has already been stolen from "
"(although cities become more resistant each time they are stolen from);\n"
" - sabotage predetermined city targets (with a reduced chance of success)."
msgstr ""
"Nì thu na leanas le brathadair cuideachd:\n"
" - sabotais air aonad nàimhdeil (a' sgriosadh an dàrna leth dhe phuingean "
"beatha), ma tha e air leacag leis fhèin agus ma tha an dà chluicheadair a' "
"cogadh ri chèile;\n"
" - puinnsean a chur ann an uisge de bhaile (a' lùghdachadh sluagh a' bhaile "
"le aonan agus a' falamhadh na sìol-lainn);\n"
" - teicneolas àraidh a ghoid (le buailteachd soirbheis nas lugha);\n"
" - teicneolas a bharrachd a ghoird air baile a ghoid thu teicneolas air "
"roimhe (ged a dh'fhàsas bailtean nas fhearr air dìon o ghoid mar sin gach "
"turas a ghoideas tu rud);\n"
" - sabotais air targaid àraidh sa bhaile (le buailteachd soirbheis nas "
"lugha)."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2081 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2370
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2158 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2185
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2257 data/royale/units.ruleset:2893
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2445
msgid ""
"A Spy that survives the more aggressive actions (sabotage, theft, inciting "
"rebellion, and poisoning) escapes to the safety of the nearest friendly city."
msgstr ""
"Ma mhaireas brathadair beò tro aon dhe na gnìomhan ionnsaigheach (sabotais, "
"goid, brosnachadh aramach agus puinnseanachadh), teichidh i dhan bhaile "
"chàirdeil as fhaisge oirre an uairsin."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2085
msgid "Spies built under a Communist government will be built as veteran."
msgstr ""
"Tòisichidh gach brathadair a thèid a thogail fo riaghaltas Comannach 'na "
"aonad seann-ghaisgeach."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2119
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Caravans can establish trade routes with your own cities or those of other "
"nations (even enemies) by traveling to them. A route's ongoing revenue is "
"doubled if the two cities involved are on different continents, and doubled "
"again if the cities are from different civilizations. This last condition "
"means the net benefit to your civilization of a trade route is the same "
"regardless of whether you own both cities or only one of them; if you only "
"own one city, trade in each city is doubled, but you only get the benefit "
"from one end of the route. Each city can support a maximum of three trade "
"routes."
msgstr ""
"A bharrachd air sin, thèid slighe malairt leantainneach a stèidheachadh a "
"bheir buannachdan dhan dà bhaile ann 's e a' cruthachadh puingean malairt "
"airson gach baile gach cuairt. Tha ìre na malairt leantainneach a' "
"meudachadh an cois meud an dà bhaile agus an t-astar eatarra; thèid a "
"dhùblachadh ma bhios an dà shìobhaltas air mòr-thirean eadar-dhealaichte "
"agus a-rithist mas ann aig dà shìobhaltas eadar-dhealaichte a tha an dà "
"bhaile. 'S ciall dhan chumha mu dheireadh seo gum faigh do shìobhaltas an "
"dearbh bhuannachd ghlan o shlighe malairt ge b' ann agad-sa tha an dà bhaile "
"gus nach eil; ma tha aonan dhiubh agad, thèid a' mhalairt anns an dà bhaile "
"a dhùblachadh ach chan fhaigh thu buannachd ach o aonan dhiubh."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2139 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2428
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2220 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2247
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2306 data/royale/units.ruleset:3146
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2504
msgid "Freight"
msgstr "Frachd"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2165 data/classic/units.ruleset:2246
msgid "The Freight unit replaces the Caravan, and moves at twice the speed."
msgstr ""
"Tha an t-aonad frachd a' dol an àite a' charabhain agus tha e dà thuras nas "
"luaithe."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2170 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2460
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2251 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2279
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2338 data/royale/units.ruleset:3178
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2536
msgid "Explorer"
msgstr "Taisgealaiche"

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2196 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2486
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2277 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2305
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2364 data/royale/units.ruleset:3204
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2562
msgid ""
"Explorers are brave individuals that are very useful for mapping unknown "
"territory."
msgstr ""
"'S e daoine curanta a tha anns na taisgealaichean a tha glè fheumail gus "
"àrainn neo-aithnichte a rùrachadh."

#: data/civ2/units.ruleset:2231 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2583
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2360 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2392
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2447 data/royale/units.ruleset:3306
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2659
msgid ""
"When a Barbarian Leader is killed on a tile without any defending units, the "
"100 gold ransom is paid, but only to land units and helicopters."
msgstr ""
"Nuair a thèid ceannard borbach a mharbhadh air leacag as aonais aonadan dìon "
"sam bith, thèid 100 pìosan de dh'òr a phàigheadh ach do dh'aonadan "
"talamhainn agus heileacoptairean."

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:81 data/classic/buildings.ruleset:81
#: data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:83 data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:80
#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:82 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:81
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Allows a city to produce veteran air units (including helicopters and "
"missiles). Also, damaged air units (again, including helicopters) which stay "
"in town for one full turn without moving are completely restored."
msgstr ""
"Bheir seo comas do bhaile aonadan adhair a thogail a bhios 'nan seann "
"ghaisgich (a' gabhail a-steach heileacoptairean).  Cuideachd, thèid aonad "
"adhair a chaidh a dhochann (a' gabhail a-steach heileacoptairean) 's a "
"dh'fhuiricheas ann am baile fad làn-chuairt gun ghluasad a shlànachadh gu "
"tur."

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:86
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Two cities with Airports can airlift one unit per turn, including aircraft. "
"Airlifting instantly transports the unit from one city to another and will "
"use all of the unit's movement points. A unit must have some movement points "
"left to be airlifted, and cannot carry cargo."
msgstr ""
"'S urrainn do dhà bhaile anns a bheil puirt-adhair togail-adhair a dhèanamh "
"le aon aonad gach cuairt.  Ma nì thu togail-adhair, thèid an t-aonad a "
"ghluasad on dàrna bhaile gun bhaile eile agus cha bhi puingean gluasaid air "
"fhàgail aig an aonad.  Feumaidh puingean gluasaid a bhith aig aonad mus "
"urrainn dhut togail-adhair a dhèanamh leis."

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:113 data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:145
#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:178 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:116
#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:150 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:185
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:115 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:147
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:180
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Allows a city to grow larger than size 8. A Sewer System is required for a "
"city to grow larger than size 16."
msgstr ""
"Bheir seo comas do bhaile fàs nas motha na 8.  Feumaidh baile rian "
"shàibhearan cuideachd mus fàs e nas motha na 12."

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:116 data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:148
#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:181 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:119
#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:153 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:188
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:118 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:150
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:183
msgid ""
"These larger cities enjoy increased defense (+50%) against both land and sea "
"units. However, such large settlements have a small risk of fire, which can "
"destroy buildings in the city."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:120 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:123
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:122
msgid ""
"Starting at size 5, growing cities incur an increasing risk of plague due to "
"overcrowding. An Aqueduct reduces that base chance by 30%."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:123 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:126
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:125
msgid ""
"Building an Aqueduct in a city without access to a lake or river requires "
"knowledge of Construction, and it costs more to build and maintain."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:129 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:132
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:131
#, fuzzy
msgid "Aqueduct, Lake"
msgstr "Duct-uisge"

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:152 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:157
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:154
msgid ""
"Starting at size 5, growing cities incur an increasing risk of plague due to "
"overcrowding. An Aqueduct, Lake reduces that base chance by 30%."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:155 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:160
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:157
msgid ""
"Aqueducts in cities with access to a lake require no special technology and "
"are cheap to build and maintain."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:161 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:166
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:163
#, fuzzy
msgid "Aqueduct, River"
msgstr "Duct-uisge"

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:185 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:192
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:187
msgid ""
"Starting at size 5, growing cities incur an increasing risk of plague due to "
"overcrowding. An Aqueduct, River reduces that base chance by 30%."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:188 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:195
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:190
msgid ""
"Aqueducts in cities with access to a river require no special technology and "
"are cheap to build and maintain."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:212
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Increases the luxury and tax output in a city by an additional 50%. With "
"both a Bank and a Marketplace in a city, the total bonus is 100%."
msgstr ""
"Cuiridh seo am meud cinneasachadh sòghalachd is cìsean a' bhaile le 50%."

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:321
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A Cathedral makes 3 unhappy citizens content in a city, making it easier to "
"maintain order in that city, However, it does not affect citizens made "
"unhappy by aggression. Knowledge of Theology increases the effect of a "
"Cathedral, making an additional unhappy citizen content, except under "
"Communism."
msgstr ""
"Nì cathair-eaglais 4 saoranaich mhì-thoilichte riaraichte ann am baile agus "
"bi e nas fhasa leis a sin rian a chumail air a' bhaile sin; ge-tà, cha bhi "
"buaidh aig a' chathair-eaglais air saoranaich a tha mì-thoilichte air sgàth "
"gnìomhachd an airm.  Nuair a lorgas tu diadhachd, cuiridh seo am meud buaidh "
"nan cathair-eaglaisean agus fàsaidh aon saoranach eile riaraichte.  Ma "
"rannsaicheas tu co-mhaoineas, lùghdaichidh seo buaidh nan cathair-eaglaisean "
"agus nì iad aon saoranach nas lugha riaraichte."

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:348
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"City Walls make it easier to defend a city. They add a +100% bonus to the "
"intrinsic defense strength of units within the city against land units. That "
"is a two-thirds increase for small cities, or a one-half increase for cities "
"larger than size 8. They are ineffective against airborne and sea units. "
"City Walls also prevent the loss of population which occurs when a defending "
"unit is defeated by a land unit."
msgstr ""
"Bidh e nas fhasa baile a dhìon ma bhios balla baile ann.  Bidh cumhachd dìon "
"de dh'aonadan am broinn baile trì turais nas àirde an aghaidh aonadan "
"talamhainn is heileacoptairean.  Chan eil iad gu feum an aghaidh aonadan "
"adhair is mara agus hòbhaitsearan.  Dìonaidh balla baile ro chall sluaigh "
"cuideachd a thachras nuair a thèid aonad dìon a sgriosadh le aonad "
"talamhainn."

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:376 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:410
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:372
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Gives a +100% bonus to the intrinsic defense strength of units within a city "
"when defending against enemy ships. For small cities the defense strength is "
"doubled by this improvement. For cities larger than size 8, it is increased "
"by two-thirds."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:384 data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:96
#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:418 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:380
msgid "Amphitheater"
msgstr "Taigh-cluich fosgailte"

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:401 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:326
msgid ""
"Entertains the citizens of a city, making 3 unhappy citizens content.  (Four "
"after the discovery of Electricity.)  However, it does not affect citizens "
"made unhappy by military activity."
msgstr ""
"Bheir seo cuirm dha na saoranaich agus nì e 3 saoranaich mhì-thoilichte "
"riaraichte.  (Ceithir às dèidh dhut dealan a rannsachadh.)  Ge-tà, cha bhi "
"buaidh aig a' choileasam air saoranaich a tha mì-thoilichte air sgàth "
"gnìomhachd an airm."

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:424 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:458
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:420
msgid ""
"Halves all kinds of waste in a city (corruption, production waste, and food "
"waste). In your capital, corruption and production waste is eliminated. A "
"Granary together with a Courthouse in a city will eliminate food waste."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:429 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:463
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:425
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Also makes one unhappy citizen content (unless that citizen is unhappy about "
"military activity), and makes the revolt cost of the city 4 times bigger."
msgstr ""
"Nì taigh-cùirte 1 saoranach mì-thoilichte riaraichte ann an deamocrasaidh "
"(ach saoranaich a tha mì-thoilichte air sgàth gnìomhachd an airm)."

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:453 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:448
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Increases the shield production in a city by 25%, or 50% with an electrical "
"plant of any kind in the same city."
msgstr ""
"Cuiridh seo am meud cinneasachadh sgiathan de bhaile le 50%.  Faodaidh am "
"meudachadh seo a chur gu mòr ris an truailleadh cuideachd."

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:456 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:490
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:451
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"This increase in production may contribute significantly to pollution. A "
"Factory also increases the pollution caused by the population of the city."
msgstr ""
"Cuiridh seo am meud cinneasachadh sgiathan de bhaile le 50%.  Faodaidh am "
"meudachadh seo a chur gu mòr ris an truailleadh cuideachd."

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:479
msgid ""
"When any small city grows or shrinks, 10 food points are saved. This helps "
"cities to grow faster and more easily withstand famine. With a Granary this "
"is extended to cities of size 4 and above. 10 food points is half what a "
"small city needs to grow, but more points are needed for later growth steps."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:485 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:517
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:480
msgid ""
"A Granary also halves the food wasted in cities far from your capital. "
"Together with a Courthouse it eliminates food waste."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:488 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:520
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:483
msgid ""
"TIP: to maximise the speed with which a city grows, you should build a "
"Granary before it grows larger than size 4."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:512 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:507
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Gives one extra food resource on all Ocean or Deep Ocean tiles, but not "
"Lakes. The city needs to be coastal (next to one of these tiles) to build "
"this improvement."
msgstr ""
"Bheir seo dhut aon ghoireas bìdh a bharrachd o gach leacag cuain.  Feumaidh "
"am baile a bhith ri taobh na mara mus urrainn dhut seo a thogail."

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:538 data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:682
#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:874 data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:1033
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Any kind of electrical plant increases the shield production effects of any "
"Factory or Mfg. Plant in its city by 25% each. Thus, an electrical plant in "
"combination with either a Factory or Mfg. Plant gives a 50% production bonus "
"over the level without any of these improvements. An electrical plant, "
"Factory, and Mfg. Plant together give a 100% production bonus. The extra "
"production may lead to the city generating more pollution."
msgstr ""
"Cuiridh seo am meud buaidh an fhactaraidh agus an taighe-saothrachaidh air "
"cinneasachadh sgiathan a' bhaile. Cuiridh taigh-cumhachd am meud "
"cinneasachadh sgiathan le 75% ma bhios factaraidh no taigh-saothrachaidh sa "
"bhaile thar na gheibheadh tu as aonais; gheibhear duais cinneasachaidh 150% "
"an cois taigh-cumhachd, factaraidh agus taigh-saothrachaidh ann am baile. "
"Faodaidh gun adhbharaich an cinneasachadh a bharrachd seo barrachd "
"truaillidh ann."

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:547 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:581
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:541
#, c-format
msgid ""
"However, a Hydro Plant also reduces the pollution associated with shield "
"production to 50% of its normal value, or 25% in combination with a "
"Recycling Center. Pollution is reduced further for the player who owns the "
"Hoover Dam. A Hydro Plant's effect is the same as that of a Nuclear Plant. "
"With the Hoover Dam, its effect is increased to that of a Solar Plant."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:554 data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:698
