#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:501 data/classic/units.ruleset:477
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:489 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:477
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:513 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:505
msgid ""
"Settlers are one of the key units in the game, as they are your main means "
"of founding new cities."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:504
msgid ""
"Settlers can also perform some of the same terrain alterations as Workers, "
"but cannot build airstrips, airbases, or buoys."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:507 data/royale/units.ruleset:519
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:511
msgid ""
"TIP: optimal production of Settlers occurs in cities of at most size 4, or "
"cities with a Granary of at most size 6."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:513 data/royale/units.ruleset:525
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:517
#, fuzzy
msgid "Migrants"
msgstr " Imrich"

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:545
msgid ""
"Migrants can be used to transfer population to other cities, but may not "
"found new cities. They can also perform some of the same terrain alterations "
"as Workers, but cannot build airstrips, airbases, or buoys."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:550 data/royale/units.ruleset:562
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:554
msgid ""
"TIP: Migrants can be a good alternative to Workers in overpopulated cities, "
"as they benefit from free food upkeep."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:556 data/classic/units.ruleset:490
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:502 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:491
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:658 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:560
msgid "?unit:Workers"
msgstr "?unit:Obraichean"

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:588 data/classic/units.ruleset:522
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:539 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:523
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:685 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:592
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Workers have the ability to improve terrain tiles. See the help on Terrain "
"and Terrain Alterations for the effects of their actions."
msgstr ""
"'S urrainn dhut do chrìochan a leudachadh le bunaitean. Faic a' chobhair air "
"'Cruth-atharrachadh de thalamh' airson barrachd fiosrachaidh."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:591 data/royale/units.ruleset:651
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:688 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:595
msgid ""
"Workers can build airstrips, airbases, and buoys, which Settlers and "
"Migrants cannot. Workers must be on board a ship to build buoys."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:622 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:626
msgid "beginner"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:622 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:626
msgid "seasoned"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:622 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:626
msgid "senior"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:622 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:626
msgid "expert"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:628 data/royale/units.ruleset:720
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:632
msgid ""
"Engineers are similar to Workers, but they work twice as fast, move twice as "
"fast, and may gain experience from work enabling them to work even faster."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:632
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"With knowledge of Fusion Power, Engineers may also perform more radical "
"terrain transformations than Workers, Settlers, or Migrants, with the "
"\"transform\" order. Examples include conversion of Tundra into Plains, or "
"even Ocean into Swamp in some circumstances, when on board an ocean-going "
"vessel, on a tile surrounded by sufficient existing land. See the Terrain "
"Alterations section for more details."
msgstr ""
"Tha einnseanairean car coltach ri obraichean ach tha iad ag obair agus a' "
"gluasad dà thuras cho luath.  'S urrainn do dh'einnseanairean talamh cruth-"
"atharrachadh cuideachd (mar eisimpleir, nì iad fàsach de thundra), rud nach "
"urrainn do thuiniche no obraiche sam bith a dhèanamh; faic an earrann air "
"'Atharrachadh na talamhainn' airson barrachd fiosrachaidh."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:732 data/royale/units.ruleset:824
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:736
#, fuzzy
msgid "Archers fight with bows and arrows and have a good offensive value."
msgstr ""
"Nì boghadairean sabaid le boghan is saighdean agus tha iad math a' toirt "
"ionnsaigh agus a' dìon."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:862 data/classic/units.ruleset:877
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:899 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:913
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:958
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Riflemen are World War-era infantry and very good at defending your cities."
msgstr ""
"'S e coisridh à àm nan cogaidhean mòra a tha ann an luchd-isnich agus tha "
"iad glè mhath ann an dìon baile."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:933 data/experimental/units.ruleset:830
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:937
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A number of Partisans are granted free when an enemy conquers your city -- "
"they automatically assume defensive positions in the surrounding countryside "
"-- but only under these conditions:\n"
"\n"
" - Guerilla Warfare must be known by at least one player.\n"
" - At least three quarters of the citizens must have your nationality.\n"
" - You must know about Communism and Gunpowder.\n"
" - You must run either a Democracy or a Communist government."
msgstr ""
"Gheibh thu grunn phartasan saor an-asgaidh nuair a cheannsaicheas nàmhaid "
"baile agad -- bheir iad orra àitichean dìon san sgìre mun cuairt air a' "
"bhaile -- ach a-mhàin san t-suidheachadh a leanas:\n"
" - Feumaidh cogadh guerilla a bhith rannsaichte aig aon chluicheadair air a' "
"char as lugha.\n"
" - Feumaidh gur thuse an neach a stèidhich am baile o thùs.\n"
" - Feumaidh eòlas a bhith agad air co-mhaoineas agus fùdar-gunna.\n"
" - Feumaidh riaghaltas deamocratach no co-mhaoineach a bhith agad."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:975 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:979
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Fundamentalist nations can maintain Fanatic units without having to pay any "
"upkeep nor causing military unhappiness.  Instead, each unit reduces the "
"population by 1."
msgstr ""
"Cumaidh nàiseanan bun-chreidmheach aonadan fanatach agus cha bhi aca "
"sgiathan beòshlaint a phàigheadh air an son."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1043 data/royale/units.ruleset:1184
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1047
msgid ""
"Paratroopers are experts at airborne attacks. From a friendly city, airbase, "
"or airstrip, Paratroopers who have not expended any movement points can "
"paradrop directly to any tile in range, and be immediately ready to act "
"there. (Beware dropping into unseen territory, as Paratroopers landing on a "
"tile occupied by enemy units are easy targets!)"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1080
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The Mechanized Infantry has the strongest inherent defensive strength of any "
"land unit, and is very fast on roads and easy terrain, but it is hindered "
"rather than helped by rough terrain. It cannot move into mountains, swamps, "
"or jungles, and it is only available near the end of the technology tree."
msgstr ""
"'S a' choisridh mheacanaichte an t-aonad talamhainn aig a bheil neart dìon "
"as àirde ach chan fhaighear seo ach aig ceann thall craobh na teicneolasan."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1148
msgid ""
"Chariots are horse-pulled war wagons. They have a stronger attack than "
"Horsemen, but their speed comes at a cost. They are more expensive to build, "
"they cannot take advantage of terrain to defend themselves, they cannot move "
"in rough terrain (mountains, swamps, and jungles) without roads, and they "
"cannot be transported by sea using early ships (Triremes and Caravels)."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1184 data/royale/units.ruleset:1327
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1188
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Elephants are towering animals trained for war that are often used as "
"powerful shock troops."
msgstr ""
"Tha ailbhein 'nam beathaichean mòra àrda a chaidh an trèanadh airson cogadh "
"agus thathar 'gan cleachdadh gus eagal a chur air nàmhaid ach chan eil iad "
"ro mhath 'gan dìon fhèin."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1342 data/royale/units.ruleset:1488
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1346
msgid ""
"Armors are motorized war wagons that are faster, stronger, and can take more "
"damage than any mounted unit. However, they are less adaptable to very rough "
"terrain (they cannot move into mountains, swamps, or jungles without roads), "
"and unable to use less rough terrain to improve their defense."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1381 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1385
msgid ""
"While powerful, Catapults (and their successors) are bulky and awkward. They "
"require roads to move in rough terrain (mountains, swamps, and jungles), are "
"difficult to defend, and are too big for early ships (Triremes and Caravels)."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1415 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1419
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Cannons are large firearms that can fire heavy projectiles over long "
"distances. As with the catapults they replace, they are very strong "
"attackers but equally weak defenders and will need an escort to be "
"effective, and have limited mobility."
msgstr ""
"'S e airm losgaidh mhòra a tha ann an canain a thilgeas airm throma thairis "
"air astar fada. Tha iad glè làidir a' toirt ionnsaigh ach chan eil ach comas "
"dìon lag annta agus feumaidh iad coimheadachd mus bi iad èifeachdach."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1449 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1453
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The artillery is an upgraded cannon. As with its predecessors, it is a very "
"strong attacker but equally weak defender and will need an escort to be "
"effective, and has limited mobility."
msgstr ""
"'S canan leasaichte a tha san airtilearaidh. Tha iad glè làidir a' toirt "
"ionnsaigh ach chan eil ach comas dìon lag annta agus feumaidh iad "
"coimheadachd mus bi iad èifeachdach."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1482 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1486
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Howitzers are upgraded artillery with improved defensive as well as "
"offensive capabilities. However, they still have the limited mobility of "
"their predecessors."
msgstr ""
"'S airtilearaidh leasaichte a tha san hòbhaitsear aig a bheil an dà chuid "
"comasan dìon is ionnsaighe nas fhearr."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1519 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1523
#, c-format
msgid ""
"Fighters and other aircraft lose 10% of their hitpoints for every turn not "
"spent in a city, airstrip, or airbase, or on a Carrier."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1555 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1559
msgid ""
"A Bomber's attack against units on land is a bombard attack. Against units "
"on water it has a regular attack."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1558 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1562
#, c-format
msgid ""
"As with other aircraft, Bombers lose 10% of their hitpoints for every turn "
"not spent in a city, airstrip, or airbase, or on a Carrier."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1593 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1597
msgid ""
"A Helicopter's attack against units on land is a bombard attack. Against "
"units on water it has a regular attack."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1596 data/royale/units.ruleset:1745
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1600
msgid ""
"Helicopters can also transport one military land unit. While most troops "
"must load or unload in a city, airstrip, or airbase (and not in the field or "
"onboard a Carrier), units specializing in mobility (Paratroopers, Alpine "
"Troops, Marines, Partisans, and Fanatics) can embark or disembark at any "
"time."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1602 data/royale/units.ruleset:1751
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1606
msgid ""
"Unlike other aircraft, Helicopters are not required to return to a city, "
"base, or Carrier to refuel after a set number of turns. However, care must "
"be exercised, due to the health they lose every turn."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1705 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1543
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1854 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1709
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The Trireme is your first boat unit. It can act as a transport ship and has "
"rudimentary offensive capabilities, and unlike later boats can travel on "
"rivers, but it may not enter deep ocean tiles."
msgstr ""
"'S e an trì-ràmhach a' chiad aonad bàta a bhios agad. 'S urrainn dha aonadan "
"a ghiùlan agus tha comas beag ionnsaigh ann ach chan urrainn dha seòladh air "
"leacagan an aiginn."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1741 data/royale/units.ruleset:2032
#, fuzzy
msgid "The Caravel is a sailing ship that can enter any ocean tile."
msgstr ""
"Tha an carbhal a' dol an àite an trì-ràmhaich agus seòlaidh e air leacag "
"cuain sam bith."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1774 data/royale/units.ruleset:2065
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1779
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The Galleon is a pure transport ship, the first which can transport large "
"wheeled units. It cannot attack other ships, though it may still defend "
"itself when attacked."
msgstr ""
"Chan eil sa ghailleon ach bàta giùlain agus chan urrainn dha ionnsaigh a "
"thoirt air bàtaichean eile ged a tha e comasach air a dhìon fhèin ma "
"bheirear ionnsaigh air-san."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1807 data/royale/units.ruleset:2098
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1812
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The Frigate is a specialized ship with a strong offensive value, and can "
"attack units on land, but it cannot transport units."
msgstr "'S e aonad bàta ionnsaigheach làidir a tha ann an crùsair."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1839 data/royale/units.ruleset:2166
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1844
#, fuzzy
msgid "The Ironclad is an armored ship, more sturdy than the Frigate."
msgstr ""
"'S e bàta cogaidh caithbheartach a tha ann am bàta iarann-sligeach agus tha "
"e fada nas bunanta na am frigead ach chan eil comas giùlain ann mar a tha "
"san fhrigead."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1875 data/royale/units.ruleset:2202
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1880
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"An improved Ironclad, with better move rate and vision. Anti-submarine "
"weapons double its defense against Submarines."
msgstr ""
"'S e bàta iarann-sligeach leasaichte a tha ann aig a bheil comas gluasaid is "
"lèirsinn nas fhearr."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:1878 data/royale/units.ruleset:2205
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1883
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"TIP: A very fast unit, which is very useful for hunting down enemy "
"Transports and Submarines."
msgstr ""
"GLIOCAS:  Aonad fìor luath a tha glè fheumail gus giùlanairean nàimhdeil a "
"shealg."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2048
msgid ""
"It can transport aircraft and military land units (not wheeled), although "
"land units cannot always be transferred to and from Helicopters while "
"onboard. See Helicopter help."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2095
msgid ""
"Transports can also clean pollution and fallout on water tiles, and with "
"knowledge of Miniaturization, may build oil platforms on deep ocean tiles, "
"for use by Offshore Platforms."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2170 data/royale/units.ruleset:2701
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2182
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You can build Nuclear units when you have the required advance, and the "
"Manhattan Project wonder has been built by any player. However, without "
"further technology they cannot move on their own."
msgstr ""
"'S urrainn dhut aonadan niùclasach a thogail nuair a bhios na h-adhartasan "
"iomchaidh agad agus nuair a bhios Pròiseact Manhatten air a thogail aig "
"cluicheadair air choireigin."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2174 data/royale/units.ruleset:2644
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2186
msgid ""
"With Advanced Flight, all Nuclear units (including those already built) gain "
"a range of 8 movement points, and Rocketry increases this to 16."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2178 data/classic/units.ruleset:1969
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:1996 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2068
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2190 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2247
msgid ""
"On impact, the blast will destroy any unit in an area 3 tiles wide (3x3 "
"squares for rectangular grids), including friendly units. Any city within "
"the blast area loses half its population, and land tiles within the blast "
"area are subject to nuclear fallout."
msgstr ""
"Nuair a bhuaileas e air an targaid, sgriosaidh e aonad sam bith ann an "
"àrainn 3 leacagan a leud (3x3 ceàrnagan air griodaichean ceart-cheàrnach), "
"a' gabhail a-steach aonadan càirdeil. Caillidh baile sam bith an broinn raon "
"an spreadhaidh an dàrna leth dhe shluaigh agus tha leacagan talamhainn am "
"broinn raon an spreadhaidh buailteach do shileadh niùclasach."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2183 data/classic/units.ruleset:1974
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2001 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2073
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2656 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2195
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2252
msgid ""
"Nuclear fallout reduces tile output and increases the risk of global nuclear "
"winter. See the help on Fallout."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2186
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"TIP: You may be involved in a situation where you've invaded an enemy "
"country en masse, but the enemy cities are too strong. Before using a "
"Nuclear unit, assemble a gang of cleanup units next to the city and have "
"them ready to fix the fallout on the same turn it occurs! This minimizes the "
"chance of nuclear winter. Eco-friendly nukes!"
msgstr ""
"GLIOCAS 2: Faodaidh gun dig latha 's tu air briseadh a-steach air dùthaich "
"le arm mòr ach bailtean nàimhdeil a tha ro làidir. Mus cleachd thu arm "
"niùclasach, cruinnich buidheann de thuinichean faisg air a' bhaile ach am bi "
"iad ri do làimh gus an sileadh niùclasach a ghlanadh san dearbh chuairt 's a "
"nochdas e! Lùghdaichidh seo cunnart de gheamhradh niùclasach. Ionnsaigh "
"niùclasach èiceolach! "

#. TRANS: diplomatic rank.
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2225 data/classic/units.ruleset:2018
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2045 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2117
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2761 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2297
#, fuzzy
msgid "?diplomatic_rank:attaché"
msgstr "?diplomatic_rank:attache"

#. TRANS: diplomatic rank
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2227 data/classic/units.ruleset:2020
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2047 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2119
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2763 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2299
msgid "?diplomatic_rank:secretary"
msgstr "?diplomatic_rank:rùnaire"

#. TRANS: diplomatic rank
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2229 data/classic/units.ruleset:2022
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2049 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2121
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2765 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2301
msgid "?diplomatic_rank:envoy"
msgstr "?diplomatic_rank:teachdaire"

#. TRANS: diplomatic rank
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2231 data/classic/units.ruleset:2024
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2051 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2123
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2767 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2303
msgid "?diplomatic_rank:ambassador"
msgstr "?diplomatic_rank:tosgaire"

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2243 data/royale/units.ruleset:2779
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2315
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Many covert actions may be attempted even in peacetime, but the more "
"aggressive actions will be discovered and cause diplomatic incidents, giving "
"an excuse for the breaking of treaties by a Federation or Democracy, or a "
"nuclear-armed regime otherwise restrained by the United Nations."
msgstr ""
"'S urrainn dhut grunn ghnìomhan dìomhair fheuchainn fiù rè àm sìthe ach "
"mothaichear dha na gnìomhan a tha glè ionnsaigheach agus adhbharaichidh iad "
"connspaid dhìoplomasach agus bheir seo cothrom do phoblachdan is "
"deamocrasaidhean cùmhnantan a bhriseadh."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2249 data/royale/units.ruleset:2785
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2321
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If a foreign unit is alone on a tile, you may attempt to bribe it with your "
"Diplomat. By paying a sum of gold the unit will immediately become yours. "
"The exact sum depends on the status of the unit and that of the civilization "
"owning it. However, units belonging to Republican or Democratic governments "
"cannot be bribed. Bribery when not at war will cause a diplomatic incident."
msgstr ""
"Ma bhios aonad cèin air leacag leis fhèin, 's urrainn dhut feuchainn ri brìb "
"a thoirt dha leis an dìoplomat agad. Le bhith a' pàigheadh suim a dh'òr, "
"bidh an t-aonad agad-sa sa bhad; tha an t-suim fhèin a' crochadh air staid "
"an aonaid agus an t-sìobhaltais aig a bheil e. Chan urrainn dhut aonadan a "
"tha aig riaghaltas deamocrasach a bhrìbeadh ge-tà. Ma bhrìbeas tu aonad rè "
"àm sìthe, adhbharaichidh tu connspaid dhìoplomasach."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2256
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Diplomats can also perform a number of actions in another player's city, "
"although each Diplomat may attempt only one action. Most of these actions "
"have a chance of failure. Also, any enemy Diplomats or Spies in the city "
"will oppose hostile actions, as will the enemy Leader in games with leaders. "
"In this case, either your unit or the defending unit will die. If you go up "
"against the Leader you will always die. If the defending unit dies, you lose "
"one movement point and may try again."
msgstr ""
"'S urrainn do dhìoplomat grunn rudan a dhèanamh ann am baile aig "
"cluicheadair eile ach chan fhaod gach aon dhiubh rud a dhèanamh ach aon "
"turas. Fàilligidh na gnìomhan seo uaireannan. Cuideachd, 's urrainn do "
"dhìoplomatan agus brathadairean sa bhaile sin ceann a thoirt do ghnìomhan "
"nàimhdeil; ma thachras seo, bàsaichidh an t-aonad agad-sa no an t-aonad a "
"tha a' cur ceann dhut. Ma bhàsaicheas an t-aonad a tha a' dìon, caillidh "
"thusa aon phuing gluasaid agus 's urrainn dhut feuchainn ris a-rithist."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2266 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2493
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2338 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2569
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
" - \"Establish Embassy\": This action always succeeds, and gives permanent "
"contact with the city's owner, as well as intelligence on their national "
"budget and technology. Each player you have an embassy with that knows a "
"technology reduces that technology's research cost to you."
msgstr ""
" - \"Stèidhich ambasaid\": Thèid leis a' ghnìomh seo an-còmhnaidh agus bheir "
"e dhut conaltradh seasmhach leis an t-sìobhaltas aig a bheil am baile agus "
"fàisneis air an cuid chìsean is teicneolais."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2289 data/royale/units.ruleset:2817
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2361
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
" - \"Incite a Revolt\": In return for gold a foreign city will change "
"allegiance and join your empire, bringing along all nearby units that call "
"it home, but reducing its size by 1. Units in other cities remain in the "
"enemy's control, but units outside cities are lost to both players. The "
"exact sum depends on the status of the city and that of the civilization "
"that owns it. It is not possible to incite a rebellion in a capital, or in "
"any city governed by a Federation or Democracy. Incitement may be attempted "
"in peacetime, but will cause a diplomatic incident."
msgstr ""
" - \"Brosnaich aramach\": 'S urrainn dhut òr a phàigheadh do bhaile ach am "
"fàg iad an sìobhaltas eile 's gus an lean iad riut-sa, a' toirt leotha gach "
"aonad a tha an dachaigh ann, ged a thèid meud a' bhaile a lùghdachadh le 1. "
"Bidh aonadan ann am bailtean eile fo smachd do nàmhaid fhathast ach thèid "
"aonadan taobh a-muigh bhailtean air chall 's cha bhi iad aig aon seach aon "
"dhiubh. Tha an t-suim a' crochadh air staid a' bhaile agus an t-sìobhaltais "
"aig a bheil e. Chan urrainn dhut aramach a bhrosnachadh ann am prìomh bhaile "
"no ann am baile sam bith a tha aig deamocrasaidh. 'S urrainn dhut feuchainn "
"ri aramach a bhrosnachadh fiù nuair a bhios sìth ann ach adhbharaichidh tu "
"connspaid dhìoplomasach."

#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2303 data/royale/units.ruleset:2831
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2375
#, fuzzy
