#. TRANS: Legend for nation in "core" set
#: data/nation/austrian.ruleset:9
msgid ""
"The origins of Austria date back to the time of the Roman Empire when a "
"Celtic kingdom was conquered by the Romans in approximately 15 BCE, and "
"later became Noricum, a Roman province, in the mid 1st century CE - an area "
"which mostly encloses today's Austria. In 788 CE, the Frankish king "
"Charlemagne conquered the area, and introduced Christianity. Under the "
"native Habsburg dynasty, Austria became one of the great powers of Europe. "
"In 1867, the Austrian Empire was reformed into Austria-Hungary. The Austro-"
"Hungarian Empire collapsed in 1918 with the end of World War I. After "
"establishing the First Austrian Republic in 1919, Austria joined Nazi "
"Germany in the Anschluss in 1938. This lasted until the end of World War II "
"in 1945, after which Austria was occupied by the Allies."
msgstr ""
"Tha tùsan na h-Ostaire a' dol air ais gu linn Impireachd na Ròimhe nuair a "
"cheannsaich na Ròmanaich rìoghachd Cheilteach mun bhliadhna 15 RC. Rinn iad "
"Noricum dheth ann am meadhan na ciad linne, mòr-roinn Ròmanach, sgìre a "
"ghabh a-steach a chuid as motha dhen Ostair. Cheannsaich an rìgh Francach "
"Charlemagne an sgìre ann an 788 agus thug e a-steach a' Chrìostaidheachd. "
"Bha an Ostair am measg nan dùthchannan a bu chumhachdaiche san Roinn-Eòrpa "
"fo thànaisteachd dùthchasach Habsburg. Chaidh Impireachd na h-Ostaire ath "
"chruthachadh ann an 1867, breith Impireachd na h-Ostaire 's na h-Ungaire. "
"Thàinig sin gu crìoch ann an 1918 aig deireadh na Ciad Chogaidh Mhòir. "
"Dh'aoinich iad ri Gearmailt nan Nazi ann an 1938 an dèidh stèidheachadh Ciad "
"Phoblachd na h-Ostaire ann an 1919. Mhair seo gu ruige deireadh an Dàrna "
"Chogaidh Mhòir ann an 1945 nuair a ghabh an Caidreachas seilbh na dùthcha."

